## 6. Phase 5 — Premium Luxury Experience
**Goal:** Introduce refined interactions.

---

### Task 5.1: Multi-Image Card Slider / Swipe Carousel
- **Why This Matters:** A single static image forces the user to click into detail pages to see different angles.
- **Expected Impact:** Improves discovery speed by letting users preview listings from the main grid.
- **Technical Difficulty:** Medium
- **Estimated Time:** 14 Hours
- **Dependencies:** None
- **Acceptance Criteria:**
  - Replace the static card image with a hover-triggered slide control on desktop.
  - Implement absolute-positioned chevron indicators and pagination dots.
- **Priority:** P1

---

### Task 5.2: Elevating Tactile Hover States
- **Why This Matters:** Flat hover elements look plain. Premium portals use subtle shadow lifts and transitions.
- **Expected Impact:** Adds interactive refinement that matches luxury branding.
- **Technical Difficulty:** Easy
- **Estimated Time:** 4 Hours
- **Dependencies:** None
- **Acceptance Criteria:**
  - Add transition classes to listing cards (`hover:shadow-lift hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all duration-500 ease-out`).
  - Keep shadow elevations consistent across all property cards.
- **Priority:** P2

---

### Task 5.3: Cinematic Exposure Transitions (`image-in`)
- **Why This Matters:** Default browser image loading looks abrupt. A smooth fade-in adds editorial polish.
- **Expected Impact:** Enhances visual transitions on slow mobile connections.
- **Technical Difficulty:** Easy
- **Estimated Time:** 2 Hours
- **Dependencies:** None
- **Acceptance Criteria:**
  - Apply the custom `image-in` animation classes (defined in [styles.css](file:///c:/Users/Ky/cc/src/styles.css)) to all property listing images.
- **Priority:** P2

